The source code and tests with this project accompany a paper published in
and issue of Philosophical Transaction of the Royal Society, May 2009.

This is a bolt-on to Chaste release 1.1.

Please unzip this project as a bolt-on project to you main checkout of
Chaste (so that its location is ./projects/PhilTransA2009 relative to the
Chaste parent directory.

Timing results similar to the 2D barchart figures can be reproduced with
 scons build=GccOpt test_suite=projects/PhilTransA2009/test/TestCardiacFastSlowProblemForPaper2D.hpp
Timing results similar to the 3D barchart figures can be reproduced with
 scons build=GccOpt test_suite=projects/PhilTransA2009/test/TestCardiacFastSlowProblemForPaper3D.hpp 
Actual timing results were produced using an Intel compiler and the Intel
Math Kernel Library.  That is, with 
scons build=IntelProduction ... 

